    "department": "Go To Market",
    "description": "About the role\n\n\nWe are looking for a Partner AI Deployment Engineer (ADE) to own OpenAI’s senior technical engagement with McKinsey, BCG, and Bain globally. This role is the primary technical point of contact for MBB advisory partners on complex enterprise proposals and transformation programmes, ensuring that OpenAI’s platform is positioned, architected, and deployed to support board-level AI agendas.\n\nThe role sits at the intersection of strategy, architecture, and execution. You will work directly with MBB partners and principals to translate executive ambition into scalable, production-ready AI programmes built on the OpenAI platform. You will operate across multiple industries and engagements, shaping solution direction, guiding architectural decisions, and orchestrating delivery across OpenAI and partner teams.\n\nThis role is based in Munich or Dublin. We use a hybrid work model of 3 days in the office per week and offer relocation assistance to new employees.\n\nIn this role, you will:\n\n\nAct as the senior technical lead for McKinsey, BCG, and Bain across priority enterprise pursuits and transformation programmes.\n\n - Serve as the primary technical counterpart to MBB Partners and Principals during proposal development and client engagements.\n\n - Translate board-level AI strategies into executable technical architectures, delivery plans, and platform roadmaps.\n\n - Provide architectural leadership across multiple concurrent programmes, ensuring consistency, quality, and alignment with OpenAI standards.\n\n - Orchestrate ADEs and Forward Deployed Engineers (FDEs) across MBB-led engagements, engaging the right expertise at each phase.\n\n - Guide partners and customers through critical decisions on platform design, scalability, governance, safety, and reliability.\n\n - Support the development of repeatable industry solutions and transformation patterns built on the OpenAI platform.\n\n - Act as a technical escalation point during complex or high-risk phases of delivery to reduce execution risk.\n\n - Represent MBB partners internally, synthesising insights from large-scale programmes into actionable input for Product and Research teams.\n\nYou will thrive in this role if you:\n\n - Have held a highly technical role at McKinsey, BCG, or Bain (e.g., Partner, Principal, Senior Expert, or equivalent) - preferred.\n\n - Have 10+ years of experience in enterprise architecture, AI/ML platforms, solution delivery, or technology strategy.\n\n - Bring a strong combination of deep technical expertise and commercial or advisory experience.\n\n - Have led or supported large-scale enterprise transformation programmes alongside senior client executives.\n\n - Possess industry expertise in at least one of the following: Financial Services; Pharma \u0026 Life Sciences; Healthcare; Retail.\n\n - Are comfortable operating in ambiguous environments and balancing strategic intent with delivery constraints.\n\n - Can engage credibly in boardrooms, executive workshops, and deep technical design sessions.\n\n - Take ownership of outcomes and are comfortable leading without direct line authority.\n\n - Bring a collaborative mindset and enjoy working across advisory partners, product teams, and GTM organisations.\n\nAbout OpenAI\n\nOpenAI is an AI research and deployment company dedicated to ensuring that general-purpose artificial intelligence benefits all of humanity. We push the boundaries of the capabilities of AI systems and seek to safely deploy them to the world through our products. AI is an extremely powerful tool that must be created with safety and human needs at its core, and to achieve our mission, we must encompass and value the many different perspectives, voices, and experiences that form the full spectrum of humanity. \n\nWe are an equal opportunity employer, and we do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, age, veteran status, disability, genetic information, or other applicable legally protected characteristic.\n\nFor additional information, please see OpenAI’s Affirmative Action and Equal Employment Opportunity Policy Statement https://cdn.openai.com/policies/eeo-policy-statement.pdf.\n\nBackground checks for applicants will be administered in accordance with applicable law, and qualified applicants with arrest or conviction records will be considered for employment consistent with those laws, including the San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance, the Los Angeles County Fair Chance Ordinance for Employers, and the California Fair Chance Act, for US-based candidates. For unincorporated Los Angeles County workers: we reasonably believe that criminal history may have a direct, adverse and negative relationship with the following job duties, potentially resulting in the withdrawal of a conditional offer of employment: protect computer hardware entrusted to you from theft, loss or damage; return all computer hardware in your possession (including the data contained therein) upon termination of employment or end of assignment; and maintain the confidentiality of proprietary, confidential, and non-public information. In addition, job duties require access to secure and protected information technology systems and related data security obligations.\n\nTo notify OpenAI that you believe this job posting is non-compliant, please submit a report through this form https://form.asana.com/?d=57018692298241\u0026k=5MqR40fZd7jlxVUh5J-UeA. No response will be provided to inquiries unrelated to job posting compliance.\n\nWe are committed to providing reasonable accommodations to applicants with disabilities, and requests can be made via this link https://form.asana.com/?k=bQ7w9h3iexRlicUdWRiwvg\u0026d=57018692298241.\n\nOpenAI Global Applicant Privacy Policy https://cdn.openai.com/policies/global-employee-and-contractor-privacy-policy.pdf\n\nAt OpenAI, we believe artificial intelligence has the potential to help people solve immense global challenges, and we want the upside of AI to be widely shared. Join us in shaping the future of technology.",
